Hi friends! 👋 It's been a while so I thought it would be a good time for a re-introduction. If you’re new to my page, welcome, and thanks so much for following me! I thought it would be fun to share some random facts about me!

🔹 I used to be a video game designer in Shanghai, China. However, I knew it was not the kind of art I love to create. In the summer of 2009, I packed my bag, quit my job, had a very sad breakup, and flew 7364 miles to NYC. Why? Because my true passion is creating fun and fashionable art for women, not bloody monsters in video games and I knew NYC was a great starting point to chase my dream.

🔹 My Chinese last name is Du spelled D U. When I would give it to open accounts, people would always pause and be like “that’s it?”

🔹 Now I live in Houston, TX with my sweet husband and my soon to be 3-year-old son, his name is Ronan. I get to be my own boss, work every day as a full-time artist creating art to inspire, and empower women all around the world to chase their dreams and be the best version of themselves! 🏆

🔹 My favorite place I’ve traveled was Turkey. I went for my honeymoon and my husband lost his wedding ring after being married only 8 days when he went swimming in the Mediterranean sea! 

🔹 My favorite show is Friends! It's one of the reasons I picked New York City to start my fashion illustration career. 🗽

Tell me about yourself in the comments!

Happy Monday my friend! ⁠
Do you feel stuck on the progress to achieve your goals❓
⁠
💬 Here is a quote by Albert Einstein:⁠
"We can not solve our problems with the same thinking we used when we created them. "⁠
⁠
You have to overcome the mindset blocks and limiting beliefs in order to break through. ⁠
⁠
🙅🏻‍♀️ I used to believe that in order to be liked, I need to be a people pleaser. However, it's impossible to please everyone and make everyone like me. There will always be people who are not happy with what I did. And that's totally fine! ⁠
⁠
✅ So the new mindset should be: put me, my family, and my business goals in the front and center. Don't let others' opinions drag me down!⁠
⁠
🥳 I know I am not alone, what kind of old mindset do you need to throw out of the window? Isn't the feeling of freedom so good?😋⁠
⁠
⁠

Why we are OBSESSED with Stickers?

Stickers are not just cute and colorful, they’re a fun and playful way to express our personalities and interests. We can stick them on our laptops, water bottles, and notebooks to showcase our unique identities. Stickers can also promote our favorite brands and causes, make statements about our beliefs, and even be used as positive reinforcement and rewards. They provide a creative outlet for our artistic expressions and make searching for the perfect design a fun and exciting activity. So next time you peel off a sticker, remember that it’s more than just a simple decoration - it’s a fun way to connect with the world and showcase your individuality!

Do you know the lesser-known story about the Little Mermaid?In Hans Christian Andersen’s original tale, the Little Mermaid’s story doesn’t end with her becoming human and marrying the prince.Instead, the sea witch who granted her legs in exchange for her voice warned her that every step she took would feel like she was walking on sharp knives, and that she would only survive if the prince loved her enough to marry her.

Unfortunately, the prince did not love the Little Mermaid as she had hoped. Instead, he saw her as a dear friend and eventually married a princess from a neighboring kingdom. The Little Mermaid’s heart was broken, and she was faced with the prospect of turning into sea-foam at the break of dawn.

A group of mermaids appeared to her, carrying a knife.If the Little Mermaid killed the prince with the knife and let his blood drip onto her feet, she would become a mermaid again,The Little Mermaid couldn’t bring herself to kill the prince,Instead, she threw herself into the sea just as the first rays of dawn appeared, and her body dissolved into foam.

It’s a tale of love, courage, and sacrifice that’s sure to captivate and inspire. that’ll make you think about what you would do for the ones you love.

Dear Friend,

I know you might be reading this while carrying a weight that feels too heavy, navigating a storm that seems endless. 

I want you to know that it’s okay to feel this way. It’s okay to have moments, days, or even longer periods when everything feels overwhelming, when the light at the end of the tunnel seems dim.🌟

I understand the courage it takes to face each day, the strength it requires to simply exist when your mind is a battlefield. You might feel isolated in your struggles, but please remember, you are far from being alone 🤝. Many of us are silently walking similar paths, carrying our own invisible burdens.

It’s okay to not always be the strongest version of yourself. It’s okay to cry, to feel vulnerable, to reach out for help. These actions do not make you weak; they make you human. Remember, every step you take, no matter how small, is progress. Every breath you take in the midst of your struggles is a testament to your resilience.

Your feelings are valid, your experiences are real, and your mental health matters. You don’t have to have it all figured out. It’s okay to be a work in progress, to learn, to grow, to stumble, and to rise again.

In moments of doubt, remember this: You are important. Your presence in this world makes a difference, a unique contribution that only you can provide. Hold on to hope, even if it’s just a glimmer. The world is brighter with you in it.💕

With warmth and understanding,

Rongrong

➡️ How I make my art into planners and stickers ! 

Most people don’t realize that turning your art into sticker books is a long process! First, I chose a topic, create a mood board, and pick out a color palette. Next, I have to decide what to draw for this collection to embody the vibe. Finally, it’s the fun part! I spend about 7-10 days creating 20-30 pieces of art! It’s a whole collection shrunk down into stickers! 

After drawing, I spend the next few days scanning my art and changing color combos on procreate. Everything then is handed over to my graphic designer so she can put them into a book. They are sent to my factory to produce, which takes 60 days, and all the new sticker books are sent to my warehouse. The whole thing takes 80 days!
